This paper deals with learning robot tasks using deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of simulation for learning, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of physics parameters for the simulator, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of visual information for the robot task, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV).
